eak]], Hong Kong\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2019<ref>{{cite news|url= https://hk.asiatatler.com/dining/gordon-ramsay-maze-grill-hong-kong-interview|title=After Decades In The Business, What\u2019s Next For Gordon Ramsay?|accessdate=29 January 2019|work=Hong Kong Tatler|first=Charmaine|last=Mok|date=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |\n|-\n| ''Bread Street Kitchen\n| [[Marina Bay, Singapore]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 19 June 2015<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.herworldplus.com/lifestyle/food/4-things-know-about-gordon-ramsay%E2%80%99s-new-restaurant-bar-singapore |title= Gordon Ramsay's new restaurant is finally open in Singapore |accessdate=22 June 2015 |work= herworldPLUS |first=Xinying |last=Hong |location=Singapore |date=19 June 2015}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |\n|-\n| ''Bread Street Kitchen''\n| [[Atlantis, The Palm]], [[Dubai]], United Arab Emirates\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | \n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | Fall 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eater.com/2015/6/8/8747509/gordon-ramsay-new-restaurant-dubai|title=Gordon Ramsay to Open New Restaurant in Dubai|first=Khushbu|last= Shah|work=Eater|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Boiling Point (1998 miniseries)|Boiling Point]]'' (5-part documentary) ([[Channel Four|Channel 4]], 1998)\n* ''Beyond Boiling Point'' (6-part documentary) ([[Channel Four|Channel 4]], 2000)\n* ''Ramsay&nbsp;\u2013 Trouble at the Top'' (documentary about him taking over the Connaught Hotel restaurant, 2002)\n* ''[[Hell's Kitchen: The Game]]'' (video game, 2008)\n* ''[[Love's Kitchen]]'' (feature film, 2011)\n* ''[[Smurfs: The Lost Village]]'' (feature film, 2017) - Baker Smurf\n\n==Television appearances==\n{{more citations needed|section|date=May 2018}}\n[[File:Ramsay and U.S. Coast Guard in Miami.jpg|thumb|right|Ramsay and [[U.S. Coast Gua