liament constituency)|Glasgow Govan]] (1988-1992) <br><small>MP for [[South Ayrshire (UK Parliament constituency)|South Ayrshire]] (1970-1979)</small>\n|22 September 1991<ref name=\":9\" />\n|25 September 1992<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Allan Macartney]]<br><small>(1941-1998)</small>\n|[[File:Male portrait placeholder cropped.jpg|128x128px]]\n|MEP for [[North East Scotland (European Parliament constituency)|North East Scotland]] (1994-1998)\n|25 September 1992<ref name=\":10\" />\n|25 August 1998<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[John Swinney]] <br><small>(b. 1964)</small>\n|[[File:John Swinney, Deputy First Minister.png|85x85px]]\n|MSP for [[North Tayside (Scottish Parliament constituency)|North Tayside]] (1999-2011)<br><small>MP for [[North Tayside (UK Parliament constituency)|North Tayside]] (1997-2001)</small>\n|25 August 1998<ref name=\":11\" />\n|26 September [[2000 Scottish National Party leadership election|2000]]\n|-\n|[[Roseanna Cunningham]]<br><small>(b. 1951)</small>\n|[[File:Cabinet Secretary for the Environment, Climate Change and Land Reform, Roseanna Cunningham.png|alt=|85x85px]]\n|MSP for [[Perthshire South and Kinross-shire (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Perthshire South and Kinross-shire]] (since 2011) <br><small>MSP for [[Perth (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Perth]] (1999-2011)</small> <br><small>MP for [[Perth (UK Parliament constituency)|Perth]] (1997-2001)</small> <br><small>MP for [[Perth and Kinross (UK Parliament constituency)|Perth and Kinross]] (1995-1997)</small>\n|26 September [[2000 Scottish National Party leadership election|2000]]\n|3 September [[2004 Scottish National Party leadership election|2004]]\n|-\n|<small>[[The Right Honourable|The Right Hon.]]</small> [[Nicola Sturgeon]]<br><small>(b. 1970)</small> \n|[[File:Nicola Sturgeon election infobox 3.jpg|115x115px]]\n|[[Deputy First Minister of Scotland|Deputy First Minister]] (2007-2014) <br><small>MSP for [[Glasgow Southside (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Southside]] (since 2011)</small> <br><small>MSP for [[Glasgow Govan (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Govan]] (2007-2011)</small> <br><small>MSP for [[Glasgow (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|Glasgow]] (1999-2007)</small>\n|3 September [[2004 Scottish National Party leadership election|2004]]\n|14 November [[2014 Scottish National Party leadership election|2014]]\n|-\n|Stewart Hosie<br><small>(b. 1963)</small>\n|[[File:Official portrait of Stewart Hosie crop 2.jpg|alt=|112x112px]]\n|MP for [[Dundee East (UK Parliament constituency)|Dundee East]] (since 2005) \n|14 November [[2014 Scottish National Party leadership election|2014]]\n|13 October [[2016 Scottish National Party depute leadership election|2016]]\n|-\n|<small>[[The Right Honourable|The Right Hon.]]</small> [[Angus Robertson]] <br><small>(b. 1969)</small> \n|[[File:ABS Bild Robertson Tiroch Colin (cropped).jpg|alt=|109x109px]]\n|MP for [[Moray (UK Parliament constituency)|Moray]] (2001-2017)\n|13 October [[2016 Scottish National Party depute leadership election|2016]]\n|8 June [[2018 Scottish National Party depute leadership election|2018]]\n|-\n|[[Keith Brown (Scottish politician)|Keith Brown]]<br><small>(b. 1961)</small>\n|[[File:Cabinet Secretary for the Economy, Jobs and Fair Work, Keith Brown.png|alt=|84x84px]]\n|MSP for [[Clackmannanshire and Dunblane (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Clackmannanshire and Dunblane]] (since 2011) <br><small>MSP for [[Ochil (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Ochil]] (2007-2011)</small> <br><small>Leader of [[Clackmannanshire|Clackmannanshire Council]] (2003-2007)</small> <br><small>Councillor for [[Alva, Clackmannanshire|Alva]] (1999-2007)</small>\n|8 June [[2018 Scottish National Par