urgh East]])</small>\n|[[File:Official portrait of Tommy Sheppard MP crop 3.jpg|85x85px]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Present elected representatives ==\n\n===Members of the Scottish Parliament===\n{{see also|List of Scottish National Party MSPs}}\n\n===Members of Parliament===\n{{see also|List of Scottish National Party MPs|List of MPs for constituencies in Scotland (2019\u2013present)}}\n\n===Councillors===\nThe SNP had 431 [[councillor]]s in [[local government in Scotland|Local Government]] elected from the [[2017 Scottish local elections]].\n\n==Electoral performance==\n\n=== Scottish Parliament ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Year<ref name=\"The Scottish National Party\">{{cite web |url=http://www.historylearningsite.co.uk/scottish_national_party.htm |title=The Scottish National Party |publisher=Historylearningsite.co.uk |date=30 March 2007 |accessdate=20 April 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231210732/http://www.historylearningsite.co.uk/scottish_national_party.htm |archivedate=31 December 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n! rowspan=2|Leader\n! colspan=\"2\" |Regional Members\n! colspan=\"2\" |Constituency Members\n! rowspan=2|Total seats\n! rowspan=2|Change\n! rowspan=2|Position\n! rowspan=2|Government\n|-\n!%\n!Seats\n! %\n! Seats\n|-\n|[[1999 Scottish Parliament election|1999]]\n|[[Alex Salmond]] <br><small>MSP for [[Banff and Buchan (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Banff and Buchan]]</small>\n|27.3%\n|{{Composition bar|28|56|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}\n|28.7%\n|{{Composition bar|7|73|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}\n|{{Composition bar|35|129|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}}\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|{{no2|[[Scottish Labour|Labour]]\u2013[[Scottish Liberal Democrats|Lib Dem]] coalition}}\n|-\n|[[2003 Scottish Parliament election|2003]]\n|[[John Swinney]] <br><small>MSP for [[North Tayside (Scottish Parliament constituenc