d under the [[single transferable vote]]).\n|-\n| [[2012 Scottish local elections|2012]]||32.3% (first preference)||{{Composition bar|425|1223|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Largest party in local government; received largest number of first preference votes.\n|-\n| [[2017 Scottish local elections|2017]]||32.3% (first preference)||{{Composition bar|431|1227|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Largest party in local government; received largest number of first preference votes. <br>Best ever SNP local election result.\n|}\n\n===European Parliament (1979-2020)===\n[[File:2019 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom area results (Scotland).svg|thumb|The SNP achieved pluralities in all mainland council areas in [[2019 European Parliament election|2019]].]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Election<ref name=\"The Scottish National Party\"/>\n! colspan=\"3\" |Party Group!! Share of votes\n!Seats won\n!Notes\n|-\n| [[1979 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1979]]\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{European Progressive Democrats/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[European Progressive Democrats|EPD]]\n|19.4%||{{Composition bar|1|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1984 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1984]]\n|[[European Democratic Alliance|EDA]]\n||{{decrease}} 17.8% ||{{Composition bar|1|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1989 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1989]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{Rainbow Group (1984-1989)/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[Rainbow Group (1989-1994)|RG]]\n||{{increase}} 25.6% ||{{Composition bar|1|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1994 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1994]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{European Radical Alliance/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[European Radical Alliance|ERA]]\n|{{increase}} 32.6%||{{Composition bar|2|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||\n|-\n| [[1999 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1999]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"background:{{Greens-European Free Alliance/meta/color}};\" |\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"background:{{European Free Alliance/meta/color}};\" |\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Greens-European Free Alliance|G-EFA]]\n|{{decrease}} 27.2%\n||{{Composition bar|2|8|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Proportional representation introduced.\n|-\n| [[2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2004]]\n|{{decrease}} 19.7%\n||{{Composition bar|2|7|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}|| \n|-\n|[[2009 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2009]]\n|{{increase}} 29.1%\n||{{Composition bar|2|6|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Plurality of votes for first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/8088358.stm|title=Salmond hails 'historic' Euro win|date=8 June 2009|accessdate=8 June 2009|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090608013122/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/8088358.stm|archive-date=8 June 2009|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2014 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2014]]\n|{{decrease}} 29.0%\n||{{Composition bar|2|6|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||SNP won a plurality within Scotland.\n|-\n| [[2019 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2019]]\n|{{increase}} 37.8%\n||{{Composition bar|3|6|background-color=#DDDDDD|{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}}}||Last European election before [[Brexit]]. <br>Best ever result for SNP in both seats and vote share.\n|}\n\n===Two-tier Local Councils (1975-1996)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"4\" |District Councils\n! colspan=\"4\" |Regional and Island Councils\n|-\n! Year<ref name=\"The Scottis